title: For Sale:  Savage 1899 Takedown
postcontent: This is a very nice,high condition Savage model 1899 lever action, straight grip, with the desireable carbine buttplate, chambered for the excellent .300 Savage cartridge.  Savage offered many options on these rifles, so you won't typically find them all listed in the Blue Book, but this rifle is an 1899 Model, made in the late 1920s'. It may be a transition model,as Savage was begining to change to the 99 -  the receiver is marked 1899 has the takedown feature, a carbine buttstock( the carbines were made during this time and are more rare)  a 24" barrel with an excellent bore,sharp lands, clean and bright.  The action is tight and crisp,very positive lock up. Some nice case colors remain on the lever, the blueing is fading a little and has some light carry wear. It has a Redfield rear tang and I think a Lyman front sight. The wood is nice looking, tight, probably has had a coat of varnish added years ago, overall a very nice surviving rifle from the depression era 1920's.  *** You must be able to legally own and be willing to show drivers license, bill of sale***  Possible trades considered for similar,older quality firearms - No need to offer a low ball offer, Thanks

Wanting to see what's out there to trade on would really like another glock but open for other offers. but will sale everything for 350 also. Real nice gun. Not hurting for the money so no low balls please and I also have a couple .22 revolver as well just email me with what you have thanks for your time
